ant and representative information.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aJapanese languagexDialectsxHistory. 0aRyukyuan languagevHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aRyukyuan languagexDialects. 0aRyukyuan languagexGrammar, ComparativexJapanese. 0aRyukyuan languagexGrammar. 0aRyukyuan languagexTerms and phrases. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aGrammar Writing.  aHistorical Linguistics.  aLanguage Endangerment.  aLanguage Revival and Revitalization.  aRyukyuan Languages.1 aAnderson, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAoi, Hayato, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArakaki, Tomoko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAso, Reiko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBentley, John R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGillan, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriesenhofer, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHara, Kiyoshi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinrich, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinrich, Patrick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKageyama, Taro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarimata, Shigehisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKádár, Dániel Z., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLau, Tyler, econtributor